Motherhood is difficult, and more so when it comes to being a single mother. It's not just hard on them but also on children they single-handedly raise. To fill the void of a father, this Texas mom dressed up as a man to attend her son's 'Donuts with Dads' school breakfast.

Yevette Vasquez of Fort Worth, North Texas, donned everything from a baseball cap to a plaid shirt and topped it off with a fake mustache and dash of cologne. In a Facebook post, she said that while dropping off her son, Elijah, at the school, she noticed the parking lot filled with more cars than usual.

Just as he said it was 'Donuts with Dad' day at school, Vasquez rushed back home because she didn't want him to 'miss out' on the event. She quickly embraced a man's avatar, just for a day.

The creative single mother concludes the post with a heartwarming message: "I know seeing other dads with their kids isn't easy for mine, but it's life; at least I can do whatever it takes to put a smile on that face."

This mother definitely deserves the 'Single Ladies' salute!
